WorkItem.Description:
When in the regional settings of the computer the decimal symbol is set to , (for example in the Netherlands) Chirpy generates a comma instead of a dot in decimals when minifying javascript with for example the YUI engine. I fixed the problem with this:

System.Threading.Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentUICulture = CultureInfo.InvariantCulture;
            System.Threading.Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture = CultureInfo.InvariantCulture; 

in void OnConnection(object application, ext_ConnectMode connectMode, object addInInst, ref Array custom) of Chirp.cs. I don't know if this the best location for it, but not commas are generated anymore...
